title: For Sale:  SOLD
postcontent:
For sale is a vintage 1954 Remington 879-TC Wingmaster 12ga shotgun (I checked the serial # with Remington on the phone to verify the date). Remington began producing the 870 in 1951, so this is one of the earliest years. As a result of being older, the action is very smooth, loose, and well-broken in. It functions perfectly and handles everything fed to it. These were the days of excellent craftsmanship and quality. Unfortunately they just don't make them this way anymore. 

The gun has a few surface rust and wear spots here and there, but it is mostly in good condition. The forearm is a little loose and needs to be tightened, but I don't have a wrench to do so--that would be a 15 second fix. Due to the small surface rust spots and the loose action and forearm, I would rate this shotgun at approximately 75% of its original condition. The stock is a folding ATI stock, and the barrel is an 18.5" barrel. The stock/barrel combo mske it perfect for home defense! 

If interested, please call or text me at (8six5-7sixsix-7555). The price is negotiable. I am not looking for any trades. Please NO emails! I do not check it, so you probably won't a get a reply until next year. I will ship through your FFL if you are not local. Thanks for looking and God bless!

title: For Sale:  VLTOR Basic EMOD MilSpec Stock - Black  & FDE
postcontent:
The EMOD is based on the same rugged and practical design as the original Vltor Modstock - with specific features designed from lessons taken from the modern battlefield. The EMOD is about one inch longer than the original Modstock and with the rubber butt plate installed, is about a quarter of an inch longer than the CRANE SCB. The increased length of the EMOD is a major benefit when used on scoped rifles (SPR/DMR), as it increases the available comb for any given length of pull. The buttplate of the EMOD is slightly wider and longer at the toe than the regular M4 stock with a noticeable negative pitch, making transitions from the ready feel much more natural. The EMOD was given enough weight to help balance out the normally muzzle heavy feel associated with negative pitch buttstocks. The toe of the buttplate is rolled under; giving the EMOD a superior feel when the weapon is held in the "out of pocket" heads up hold. The buttplate is covered with a removable rubber buttpad that is molded over a metal strike plate. The shape of the buttplate and the rubber buttpad give a solid stock purchase in all situations. The EMOD features more storage in the removable, waterproof side compartments; the EMOD holds up to four CR123 or three AA batteries. There is also an additional weather proof compartment in the clubfoot area of the stock, this compartment can be accessed quickly and holds two AA batteries or other small parts. Constructed from the finest materials, the EMOD will stand up to the most rugged demands. The EMOD is available for either the standard "MilSpec" receiver extension tube, or for the aftermarket "Commercial" size tube. Available colors include Black, Foliage Green and Flat Dark Earth (tan). The EMOD is only available in the Clubfoot model. Product# VLAEB-M-B

title: For Sale:  VLTOR Basic IMod Clubfoot Milspec Stock - Black & FDE
postcontent:
VLTOR Basic IMod Clubfoot Milspec Stock - Black 

Improved Modstock, appropriately named the “IMod”. Since 2002, the original Modstock has become well known and respected by Military, Law-Enforcement and sports shooters worldwide. Even though the Modstock is considered the best on the market, Vltor believed it was time for improvements. The improvements are subtle but necessary. Feedback from end users will make the IMod the choice over the competition. 

When compared to the original Modstock, the IMod series is now available to fit either the Milspec or Commercial diameter receiver extension/buffer tube. Unfortunately, the IMod will not fit both receiver extensions, so when ordering, pick the correct item and part number. 

Like all Vltor stocks, the IMod is available in the three most popular colors; Black, Flat Dark Earth (tan) and Foliage Green. As with the original Modstocks, the IMod is offered in the conventional, “Standard” configuration and the unconventional, “Clubfoot” configuration. Even though the Standard model is the most well-known model amongst the shooting public, the Clubfoot version is a hybrid model that bridges the gap between tactical and prone shooting positions. In other words, the Clubfoot portion of the stock allows the shooter, with his/her off hand, to support the stock and to control the rear of the weapon, while shooting in prone or rested position. 

The improvements of the IMod are as follows: Integral, but removable non-slip buttpad (color matched to stock components) 

•Rolled/angled buttpad toe with wide traction area. This will assist in running the stock high on shoulder, making the IMod system more user friendly when using web-gear and/or body armor. 
•Improved lock paddle, making it easier to operate and making the contact surface non-slip when operating the lever. 
•Removed most sharp edges that may cause “snag points” to web-gear or other vital equipment. 
•Improved strength throughout construction of the stock chassis. This will provide maximum strength during “Mortaring exercise” or unexpected impact. 
•Integral, but removable non-slip buttpad (color matched to stock components) 

Installation note: The installation of the IMod stock should only be performed by a qualified gunsmith and/or certified armorer. 

IMOD at a glance: Details 
Design Removable rubber buttpad and storage compartments. A true Modular buttstock for the AR15/M16/M4 carbine series. 
Construction Impact and temperature resistant polymer, specially blended for Vltor. Metal components are either carbon steel or stainless steel (depending on the application) 
Compatibility Milspec IMods will only fit receiver extensions/buffer tubes with the outer diameter of 1.150”, while Commercial IMods will only fit 1.170” diameter receiver extensions. 
Weight - Nominal Less than 9.4 oz. (Milspec and Commercial with storage compartment and buttpad installed) 
Dimensions Length: 6.250” (without buttpad) 
Length: 6.626” (with buttpad) 
Width: 2.500” (with storage compartments installed)Height: 5.210” (with buttpad installed)

Color Finish All stocks have a matte (anti-reflection/glare) finish. IMods are only available in the following colors: Black, Flat Dark Earth (Tan) and Foliage Green. Foliage Green is more of a “grey” green versus Olive Drab. 
Special Features Storage capacity: Each side compartment can hold at least two AAs or three lithium CR123 3-volt batteries. The internal diameter of each compartment is 0.685”. 

Sling mounting: All Modstocks, including the IMod will accept a push-button, quick detachable sling swivel or a conventional web sling, measuring up to 1.375” in width. 

Product# VLTAIB-MC-B

SOLD but contact me if you are interested in other WW2 memorabilia. This German Army (Heer) Officer Dress Dagger model 1935 is in very good condition. This is a classic WKC Solingen piece all around from blade, crossguard and scabbard. Also includes original portepee knot, although it is fairly worn and showing it's age. title: For Sale/Trade:  Mas 36 7.5 french rifle
postcontent:
I have an all matching L series Mas-36 for sale or trade.  Serial is 67925 and everything matches.  To the best of my knowledge, it was made in 1945, but is unique in that it is built with some pre-war parts, such as the barrel and front site post.  The barrel is immaculate and looks like new with strong rifling.  The beechwood stock shows some occasional wear and markings, but nothing to be concerned about and it is also VERY SOLID AND TIGHT, no movement in the forend whatsoever, which is a concern with these rifles and barrel harmonics.  I wanted to preserve the history of the rifle and did not refinish it.  The action is very smooth, and I was surprised by the bolt.  It doesn't look ergonomic, but it is one of the fastest bolts I have ever cycled, especially when still shouldered.

It shoots 7.5x54 french, which can easily be found online or reloaded.  Surplus ammo can be found online for as low as $5 for 20 rds on stripper clips (avoid syrian ammo though, it's shitty).  You can also reload using the same load data as .308 and same powder, primers, and bullets.  Casings can EASILY be had as you can resize 6.5 swede casings, 30.06 casings, or buying PPU 7.5 brass.  This is one of the cheaper milsurp rifles to feed, aside from a 7.62x54r.

I have shot around 50 rds through this rifle with absolutely no malfunctions (except for 5 rds syrian ammo with bad primers)  It is very accurate at 100 yards, making nice round groupings with about 1-1.5 moa with french surplus ammo.  Could probably get sub moa with handloads. 

The rifle includes its original spike bayonet and a reproduction (non-leather) sling.

These rifles are somewhat rare, and definitely underrated as they never got the chance to be proven in battle with the french army. More pics available, Asking $350 OBO

title: For Sale:  Spyderco Manbug Folding Knife
postcontent:
The Spyderco ManBug Knife is a uniquely practical folder designed by founder Sal Glesser. Anyone who has ever used the LadyBug knows that it cuts with an authority far beyond its size. However, as part of Spyderco's quest for constant quality improvement, Glesser decided to make it even better. And, for anyone whose male ego made it difficult to carry a "LadyBug," he also made life easier. The is the ManBug-an amazing handy cutting tool that is more at home in larger hands while still fitting inconspicuously in a pocket or even on a keychain.
Exactly the same length as the LadyBug, the ManBug boasts a wider and slightly thicker blade for increased strength and superior edge geometry. Its full-flat-ground blade is meticulously crafted from VG-10 stainless steel for exceptional cutting performance, edge retention and corrosion resistance.
The handle features stainless steel bolsters and grey textured G-10 laminate scales. The blade is secured open with a sturdy back lock mechanism and includes a lanyard hole for easy attachment to a key chain or lanyard. 

Specifications:
Length Overall: 4.375" (111 mm)
Blade Length: 1.88" (48 mm)
Cutting Edge: 1.69" (43 mm)
Blade Steel: VG-10
Handle Material: Stainless Bolster/ Grey G-10 Scale
Closed Length: 2.5" (64 mm)
Weight: 1.6 oz. (45 g)
